values:
So going to attempt and try and do this actually posting to my livejournal thing again. Since for a long time I've only done it whenever I post up icons. I think each year I get this sudden urge be be proactive about it and all gunho! And then it just kind of fizzles out after a month.

WE'LL SEE SELF. WE'LL SEE.

Yesterday I stayed home sick but today is an actual day off. Now I kind of want to go in though in order to have the hours needed.

Regardless, I've been working on the premise for a new RP game, which would be based off of the world of Angel Beats! (the game being called After Beats!) I'm not sure that I'll ever put it up. Since I talk a lot, but it's one that I think would be a lot of fun. It's also one that I'm not sure if people would be all that interested in. Especially since I think I'd prefer it on insanejournal. I like some of the features of LJ but you can only take so much douche-baggery from the LJ admins before you start getting kind of irritated.

plus 100 free icons

Also I hate Frank with a passion.

Whether or not I actually ever get a game up of my own going (which sounds like a terrible amount of work) I do wish there were more panfandom games on IJ in general. I love Marina, but sort of needed a break? There's just so few. I'm sort of curious as to why there aren't more over there that are active and strong.

I thought I'd post up some more icons. My next Yuuki batch isn't done yet. I'm about halfway through. But I don't mind posting up a couple of the other VK characters. Also Cheshire! I RPed him for a very short amount of time. I never finished all of his icons, but they might as well be put to use. I hope everyone enjoys. If you have any suggestions for improvement please let me know! I'm always open to bettering myself. I know I'm definitely not perfect. Also last time I got very busy with RL and didn't get the chance to respond back to everyone. I didn't mean to ignore anyone! So imma just gonna say thank you belatedly! ^^;; Lastly (and I'll make a more detailed post for this later) Marina Asylum is going to be having a fourth wall event!/o/ It's over on insane journal, but if there is anyone who's interested or could make it that would be awesome! Honest, it's a really fun game and any and all VK characters (or even outside of cast is fine!) would be most loved. Or you could...you know, app *nudge nudge wink wink* Would people be bribed by a couple of icons?? If you've ever considered the place anyway I think it's a good opportunity to at least check it out. Currently in game we have Kaien, Juri, Yori, Yuuki, and Zero. Whether or not you visit to stay I think it would be a lot of fun to get several visitors for the event. Hope to see lots of people there! Pandora Hearts Cheshire: 37 Vampire Knight Kaien: 2 Kaname: 1 Sara: 7 Zero: 4

I've seen this floating around recently, and I'm sorta bored. Nothing special to add, so just a silly meme.

APPEARANCE:
I am 5'4" or shorter.
I think I'm ugly. -sometimes
I have many scars.
I tan easily. - Not.
I wish my hair was a different color.
I have friends who have never seen my natural hair color.
I have a tattoo.
I am self-conscious about my appearance.
I've had braces.
I own glasses. - And contacts too.
I'd get plastic surgery if it were 100% safe, free, scar-free.
I've been told I'm attractive by a complete stranger.
I have more than 2 piercings.
I have piercings in places besides my ears.
I have freckles.

FAMILY/HOME LIFE:
I've sworn at my parents. --Not often though. Normally with...
I've been kicked out of the house.
My biological parents are together.
I have a sibling less than one year old.
I want to have kids someday.
I have children.
I've lost a child.

EMBARRASSMENT:
I've slipped out a "lol" in a spoken conversation.
I've snorted while laughing.
I've laughed so hard I've cried.
I've glued my hand to something.
I've laughed till some kind of beverage came out of my nose.
I've had my pants rip in public.

HEALTH:
I was born with a disease/impairment.
I've had stitches.
I've broken a bone.
I've had my tonsils removed.
I've sat in a doctor’s office with a friend.
I've had my wisdom teeth removed. - I need them removed.
I had a serious surgery.
I've had chicken pox. - When I was 16 and whoa did that suck.

TRAVELING:
I've driven over 200 miles in one day. --But I wasn't the one behind the wheel.
I've been on a plane.
I've been to Canada. -  I lived on the border and my church was in Canada.
I've been to Niagara Falls.
I've been to Japan.
I've celebrated Mardi Gras in New Orleans.
I've been to Europe.
I've been to Africa.
I've been to France.

EXPERIENCES:
I've been lost in my city.
I've seen a shooting star.
I've wished on a shooting star.
I've seen a meteor shower.
I've gone out in public in my pajamas.
I've pushed all the buttons on an elevator.
I've been to a casino.
I've been skydiving.
I've gone skinny dipping.
I've played spin the bottle.
I've crashed a car.
I've been skiing.
I've been in a play.
I've met someone in person from the internet.
I've caught a snowflake on my tongue.
I've seen the Northern Lights.
I've sat on a rooftop at night.
I've played chicken.
I've played a prank on someone.
I've ridden in a taxi.
I've seen the Rocky Horror Picture Show.
I've eaten sushi.
I've been snowboarding.

RELATIONSHIPS:
I'm single.
I'm in a relationship.
I'm available.
I'm engaged.
I'm married.
I've gone on a blind date.
I've been the dumpee more than the dumper.
I miss someone right now.
I have a fear of abandonment.
I've been divorced.
I've had feelings for someone who didn't have them back.
I've told someone I loved them when I didn't.
I've told someone I didn’t love them when I did.
I've kept something from a past relationship.

SEXUALITY:
I've had a crush on someone of the same sex.
I've kissed a member of the same sex. -- On the cheek?
I've had sex with someone of the opposite sex.
I've had sex with someone of the same sex.
I've had sex with more than one person at the same time.
I am a cuddler.
I've been kissed in the rain.
I've had sex outdoors.
I've hugged a stranger.
I have kissed a stranger.
I have had sex with a stranger.

HONESTY/CRIME:
I've done something I promised someone else I wouldn't. -- It was an emergency.
I've done something I promised myself I wouldn't.
I have lied to my parents about where I am.
I am keeping a secret from the world.
I've cheated while playing a game.
I've cheated on a test.
I've run a red light.
I've been suspended from school.
I've witnessed a crime. - I was robbed in a burger king bathroom by a guy...
I've been in a fist fight.
I've been arrested.
I've shoplifted.

DRUGS/ALCOHOL:
I've consumed alcohol.
I smoke cigarettes.
I smoke pot.
I regularly drink.
I've taken painkillers when I didn’t need them.

MENTAL HEALTH:

I shut others out when I'm depressed.
I take anti-depressants.
I have an eating disorder.
I've slept an entire day when I didn't need it.
I've hurt myself on purpose.

I've woken up crying.

DEATH:
I'm afraid of dying.
I hate funerals.
I've seen someone dying.
I have attempted suicide.
Someone close to me has attempted suicide.
Someone close to me has committed suicide.

RANDOM:
I can sing well.
I've stolen a tray from a fast food restaurant.
I open up to others too easily.
I watch the news.
I don't kill bugs.
I hate hearing songs that sacrifice meaning for sake of being able to rhyme.
I curse regularly. - Ocassionally
I sing in the shower.
I am a morning person.
I paid for my cell phone ringtone.
I'm a snob about grammar.
I am a sports fanatic.
I play with my hair.
I have/had "x"s in my screen name.
I love being neat.
I love Spam.
I've copied more than 30 CDs in a day.

My favorite color is either white, yellow, pink, red or blue.

I can't sleep if there is a spider in the room.
I am really ticklish.
I love white chocolate.
I bite my nails.
I play video games.
I'm good at remembering faces.
I'm good at remembering names.
I'm good at remembering dates.
I have no idea what I want to do for the rest of my life.

Just as promised, here comes the Yuuki batch! Eh...been trying a couple new things, so hopefully they look a bit better than the last? A couple are really old in comparison to the newer ones. T-They don't look the best. But I really wanted them. Eiiitthhher way, I figured people who know the series well (at least as obsessively as I follow it) would catch those and be like...wait, whut. I primarily do my icons for my own personal RP purposes, which is why I did it. Otherwise I would have just kept her human in the scenes and colored them that way. I also attempted Kaname and Sara, which are two new characters for me to be coloring. @_@ And Z-Zero...kind of. I made a couple a long long LONGGGG time ago of him, but they were so ugly that I'm too ashamed to post them up. I'll probably try to throw a couple Zero ones up though at some point. Zero Icons intimidate me. I don't know why. Anyway, onto the icons! Vampire Knight

Okay...so having dropped is a lot harder than I thought. I still need to go back and reply to people on  . But every time I go to try and do that I get so over emotional about the whole thing that I can't... and then feel guilty over the fact. It's only been a few days and I already keep contemplating at least picking Yuuki back up...   is such an addiction. I've had so much fun there and have made a lot of wonderful friends. Even more...my characters all had such great character crew.

I keep trying to think of the plus's....I can pick someone else up maybe...and might find another good role play game. I've kind of been wanting to play Rena again...or experiment with someone new. But I don't know...it's hard. I've recently, before the drop, picked up Mikuru over at Marina Asylum and I just can't get the motivation to be very excited about it like I thought I would. I had to ask the mods if I could wait until next week to do an intro since a new character definitely deserves some enthusiasm. But I think since I just dropped two characters that...I like a thousand times more I just kind of sit here and look at her going... "Why would I have dropped them and now plan to play you...?" Gahhh. /angsts

So anyway moving on, my grandmother made a big to-do about the fact that she felt I needed to have a better coat for the winter. This is all great because at the time I was still working for the Daycare and we go outside a lot. I had a coat, but a better winter one would have been great. Problem is...she ordered it and it didn't get here until nearly a month or two later. Then...when it got here she had accidentally ordered two different coats. So...I needed to pick between the two of them and decide which one it was I wanted to keep and then mail it back to the company. As I was about to do that...she told me to not mail it back to them, and to her instead. SO finally I get up and go ship that to her...only to...get a package a couple days ago. It's the coat. Again. Apparently she decided to change her mind and that I could keep it. I-I wish my family could ever make up their mind on something.

Also something else to note...I got a phone call from my mom the other day. Apparently she is considering moving to Iowa as well. She told me that she was going to call me and talk to me a bit more about things, but I haven't gotten a phone call back. Soooo, I don't know how serious she is in considering that. My little sister keeps trying to get her to, though. I know why, since after Sam leaves it's going to be pretty lonely I think living at home alone without any family there. I worry about her for the same reason...so I don't really know what to expect. Hmm...

Trying not to be pissy today. I'm completely PMSing. (...D-Do I have any males on my flist? I can't remember.) I think that it might be partially why I'm so emotional over the drop. I always check animenewsnetwork every day just to see what is kinda of up in the anime/manga world. Lately I've been really frustrated with what went down with Christopher Handley's case. Has anyone else been following what went down with that? I just sit here with my mouth open going OMG seriously WTF America!?? I live in Iowa, and all I can say is that I'm thoroughly disgusted with our justice system. I think   made a comment about doujin before...we can only read this crap online because heaven forbid it get mailed here and the U.S postal service decide to shift through our mail. I don't even care for hentai or any of that kind of stuff. I mean...to each their own. Personally I find most of that stuff to be kind of gross. I've looked for good doujin before online and mostly come across things that turn me off completely.

In the end though it's really just the fact of the matter. This guy has been sentenced to prison for 6 months for a 'crime' in which no one was injured, hurt, or abused. The characters are drawings, not even real. Apparently if he didn't plead guilty they were threatening him with triple that sentence. It's disgusting. I mean technically any of that doujin with our favorite characters...? If you own it? That's right's for going to prison. This poor man and his family.

Fourth wall has wiped the floor with me and there is still the rest of today to go. AND I STILL OWE EVERYONE BACKTAGS.

That said, I'm loving it. 4th wall is always great, and to those I still owe tags to I'm sorry...I promise I'm going to get back to them. I'm just trying to keep up. If you haven't participated yet plz to be poking   and  ? They love you. ALSO. If you want tagged with one of my previous characters or mock accounts for the event, just let me know. I'm trying to go back and get everyone all sneaky ninja like, but it's easy to accidentally miss characters when it's moving so fast.

Fourth wall weekend coming up at  ! It would be much love to be hit once again with Vampire Knight cast or Fruits Basket cast. Even non-canon mates would be fun, so anyone not already aware of the event should stop by for the 13th and 14th! Most already know, but I play

Okay~! Step one to journal recovery...actually post.

I haven't posted any actual journal entry in I don't even know how long. (It only takes a minute to look, but meh.) I suppose icon batches don't count either. ;^;

Basically, following in Sari's footsteps I want to become better at following my friend's list and keeping in touch with everyone. I like knowing what's going on in everyone's life, so I suppose being less of a stalker and reading everyone else's entries without ever posting my own doesn't seem fair. So this is my attempt to correct that. Hullo friends~ Long time no chat. O/ Maybe I'll actually acquire a pretty layout this time. Does anyone know if insanejournal layout HTML and information works the same on LJ? I'm no good at it myself, but Kay and Li made such great temples that if they translate over I might be able to throw up something stupid myself, without having to bug Sari or Haunt.

Sitting here eating popcorn for Breakfast at 7:20 PM. What...does this say about me.

Lately I've been pretty restless when it comes to role play. I have...two characters over at   and currently three over at Marina Asylum. Not to further piggy-back off of Sari, but I want to attempt and experiment with someone new, but no one really comes to mind. I guess Alita kind of counts for that. I keep thinking I want to play my  human!Yuuki   account again somewhere though since it's still paid for. It's fun taking her from an earlier period and working up to the transformation later, too. But finding her a good home is difficult, and I feel kind of guilty since I already play her. So I don't know. I should probably experiment with some of the other characters. I'm just really picky about the characters I play. I can't ever play one unless I really adore them. Otherwise I end up dropping them. So...nng. I'm still undecided.

I looked back over at Kurosu Academy the other day. It made me pretty nostolgic. I kind of miss that style of writing. It took longer since everything was written in log style...or kind of like fan fiction. But it was a lot of fun, too. Those were the good ol' days. Now I kind of wonder how much time will pass by before someone else posts in the chat box.

I wasn't going to do another icon batch. At least not with most of my Yuuki icons since it's fun hording a couple to myself. I've had so many snagged though that at this point it doesn't really matter. And to me it's not that big of a deal. So have fifty Yuuki icons! I have more but some of them are even more crappy than my worst ones in this bunch, so until I can fix them up a bit better I'd be too ashamed posting them publicly. Please don't mind that a couple of them were from the old batch. Most should all be new. I have lots of fruits basket ones that I need to put up some time, but I'll save that for another day. And as usual I can't help but try advertise a little. If you like the series and enjoy role-playing, I encourage you to give it a shot and app at or over at Marina Asylum. At poly we have a Yuuki, Zero, Kaname, Sayori, Ichiru, and Rido. Meanwhile over at Marina we have... Yuuki, Zero, Kaname, Ichiru, Aidou, and Rido. I'd love more cast at either one. And everyone's super friendly. Personally myself, I'd love a Kaien, Ruka, Juri, or Shizuka. I'd love any cast at all though. All the characters are just so much love. Anyway, onto the actual point of the post and away from my shameless advertising! If you snag any, please just remember to credit back to . Hope you enjoy. If you have any suggestions for improvement let me know. I'm just a novice and jealous of everyone's mad skillz~! Yuuki Kurosu

Okay...so I've seen the first scan sneak peek of Vampire Knight chapter 36. DX It's Yuuki biting Kaname...apparently he had told her to drink as much as she wants (since she has been thirsty), and she doesn't really hesitate.

GAH, also...according to a Japanese board, it says that in Vampire pureblood families, incest is acceptable, and that Yuuki and Kaname have been engaged to each other since the moment they were born (it also said their parents were siblings...) I don't know how true it all is, till I see and translate the scans a bit myself...but UGH. I don't think I am liking this next chapter too much. The summary sounded like Yuuki was really thoughtless toward Zero, and I just feel so awful for his character. =( she definitely is losing points.

I don't like what I am hearing about the chapter so far. Obviously what has been leaked might be off...but... ^^; I'm crossing my fingers that it's a lot better than this. By tonight I think the scans should be out. I'll look for them for everyone when I get off work.

Sari-chan T_T I don't know if your fic will be done in time. I've been so busy recently >< and between getting my school papers and scholarships in it's been hard to work on. XD I'm still trying though. *huggles*

Okay...grr....*crosses fingers that the chapter is better*

Do you think, like...nearly two years later...if you were banned from a forum for rude/disrespectful behavior, and then committing a bunch of other plagerisms/un-cool things to do to people, you would STILL try and join that forum?

-_- That girl seriously needs to get a life. I'm tired of banning the same person all the time. LOL. It's just insane and kind of creepy. (Not to mention completely hypocrital of everything she 'preaches' all the time, but we wont even get into that O.O I can't stand those types of 'Christians'.)

Honestly, I just don't understand. Can someone please explain the point of it to me? DX

So, we've had low water pressure for the last week in a half. I didn't know if it was just because there was something wrong with the water everywhere, since my sister said one of her friends was having the same problem. Suddenly this wednesday though, some guy in a city truck pulled up, fiddled with the water, and all of a sudden the water pressure worked GREAT.

Of course it didn't last... 
 
Today the water turned off completely. We don't have a working phone at the moment either, besides my sister's cell phone, so we made the phone call at work. Oh my gosh...I'm so insulted. I would like to point out that we never got a notice...but regardless of that, I can understand that sometimes happens. What has me pissed off is that the phone rep was so over the top rude. She said that on Wednesday we 'illegally' turned on the water, and it was lucky that they had caught it...

...

WTF!? Their OWN worker came over here and TURNED THE WATER ON. I wouldn't even know how to do something like that, and being accused of stealing has me over the top mad. I wouldn't ever do anything like that, and I know that no one in this household did either, because I've been here whenever everyone else has been in the house. None of us would know how to do something like that, and wouldn't to begin with. So...15 minutes after the phone call, and much calming down from wanting to bite someone's headoff on the other line, I call back.....and it's closed. They will be closed until Monday, which means they we are stuck without any water at all until Monday.

FURTHERMORE, they closed down our account completely for "stealing' and said if we want it back up, we have to pay 60 dollars. I wanna scream, or cry or something. GRRR.

So beyond the water, and other real life things, that I don't want to get to into at the moment, lately I've been super bored. The last couple of days I haven't been able to get online much, but OMG....boreeed. Everyone has been gone or busy, I'm pretty much caught up in all my posts, and I haven't felt like working on fanfiction. So I've never been through that large of a storm before...but thanks to last night... 

WE'RE MISSING THE OUTER MOST PART OF OUR WALL! 

With wind gusts up to 69 mph, our little trailer doesn't have much of a chance. It tore off part of our outter wall, and caused a lot of damange to the front of the house. I woke up at around 3 last night to the wind and sever thunderstorm. It sounded like the house was going to blow away. 

I woke up and walked to the window in time to see a tree topple over, and something white fly past the house. 
Dropping my younger sister off to school this morning, there were dozens of trees embedded into cars, power lines, and poles knocked over, and other neighbors were flooded out. 

NOW we get to brace for it all over again for round two. Currently we're still in a wind advisory, with the wind at 30 mph. Today, starting around 3:00 PM we can expect it to be supposedly worse with hail, flash floods, tornados, sever winds, and sever thunderstorms. 

I'm glad the schools only have half a day today. The students would be getting out RIGHT as the storms are supposed to pick up again. I would have been furious with the schools otherwise. Anyway ^^; cross your fingers that we don't blow away by the end of the day today.

I was forgotten at work today. 

I called home and got a hold of my brother, and as usual asked him to tell my dad that I was ready. He told me he didn't know where he was. It was five when I got off. He told me that dad had been home just a little bit ago so he was sure it wouldn't take long, and he would just send him over when he got home. 

I had been the last person to leave, along with one of the guys up front. I told him I was sure my ride would be here soon so he didn't have to worry. So of course he took off.

The first half an hour didn't bother me so much. I always bring books with me to work, so I simply read that. 

Then an hour passed by.....

I don't have a phone. There was no one I could call, nothing close was nearby within walking distance.

Then another hour. 

"Dad should get here SOON though....he knew he needed to pick me up."

A half an hour.

I feel so stupid. I sat out there, in the dark, like an idiot forever just WAITING. Because there wasn't anything I could do. The security man finally pulled up to me as I finally stood up to begin walking home. It was obvious he felt very bad and asked if there was anything he could do, if I would like for him to call a cab.

I finally told him that I thought that sounded like a good idea.

The cab was a half an hour late.

My dad just got home. I don't have any idea what he was out doing. I'm not even going to ask. It wouldn't make a difference now.

I'm only bothered that......I was so easily forgotten.

So I've wasted an hour of what could have been sleep trying to call home, only to be ignored by my mom.

Lovely.

Escaping the magnitude of what happened that day....is very impossible, and I don't think it should be forgotten, as sad as this horrible event was. There is no way to describe the emotion, the pain and horror so many people felt that day, here in

America. I saw the terror on people's faces. I heard the cries of horror and anguish, watched for weeks the grief and desperation people felt as they held up pictures of their loved ones, hoping against hope that some one might have seen their husband or wife, their brother or sister, child, or best friend. So many thousands of innocent lives were taken that day, out of an act of hate. Here, even five years later, I can't help but cry remembering.

 Today should be a day of remembrance.

Last night I watched several documentaries, and today am trying to do what I can for America....to show respect to all those were killed within the terrorist attacks, honor the families of those left behind, and show my support and love for my country. Even if it is only small, I know it makes a difference.

I remember first learning about the attacks. I was in school, and was just coming out of my math class. A girl, I didn't normally talk to but was friends with, came running down the halls to me. She looked so shocked and upset. Her firsts words were "Oh my God Heather, the world trade center has been hit!"

I didn't know what to think, it seemed, at the time, like such a far fetched thing to say, except that she had seemed so genuinely upset by it. From there, I walked into my history class....and froze in horror as all those who were in the class...watched the news, feeling utterly helpless as a second plane flew into the first tower. The emotion that welled up within the room had been an almost tangible thing. You could feel it thick in the air, because this terrible event was unfolding before us....and there, within our Junior High in Traverse City, Michigan, couldn't do anything about it.

Immediately after, an announcement was made by the head of our school. She told all the teachers to turn of their televisions and resume their normal schedules. I was in history class however....of course our teacher kept it on for as long as possible, before each room was checked to make sure the televisions were off.

I didn't hear much else until I got home, and immediately turned on the T.V. It happened that as soon as I turned it on....they were showing clips of few individuals jumping from the upper floors. I just burst out into tears and had to turn it to another news station. I couldn't take watching those people in the last few seconds of their life. 

I sat in my living room all day and night, praying as hard as I could that there would be survivors. That God would protect those firemen trying to rescue those buried beneath the debris and rubble. I couldn't understand how any one could ever be so hateful....that they would attack those defenseless....without guns.... just normal citizens going to work every day, trying to provide for their families, never having expected to be hurt in such a terrible way. 

I never used to watch the news until 9/11. I'd watch each day, hoping that more survivors would be pulled free. I remember watching the tear stained faces of families who stood on the ends of streets, holding signs of their loved ones, and searching desperately for any sort of word from the firemen and police. It was the most heart wrenching thing I had ever seen, and I felt awful for all the places in the world where things like this are a common place, realizing just how much pain they must experience.

Traverse City held a memorial service, and my entire family went. Everyone was given a candle, and we brought a small flag with us. It was so small, and we felt very helpless.....but it was all we could do besides pray. 

Thank you so much to firemen, the police, and the citizens who of their own free will offered a hand in the recovery and clean up process. Thank you to those who lost their lives in the plane crash that stopped the terrorists from further hurting our country and to the men and woman who lost their lives, and their families. We will never forget, and you will never be forgotten. 

Heather

Hmm, okay, so I read a spoiler over at FruityGroup for chapter 130.

Oh lordy, I can already see the reaction from fans now. ^^; Hide Takaya-sensei hide! Mad Shikito fans on the loose! 

I don't expect a lot of shikito fans to be too happy if the summary I read was correct. I've already heard from a few people who have told me that they are disappointed, and I suppose I could understand why. If it was my Kyouru....I would have been devestated. But...since it's not....XD 

To the chapter as a whole!!

I guess I don't really understand WHAT the promise was....because I think out of all of them, considering how much Yuki wanted out of the Sohma household, he would have gladly broken it. ^^; He didn't enjoy being a Sohma, didn't want to stay by God's side, and disliked being a rat. Kyaaa, moving onto everyone's favorite...(ahaha, or mine anyway!)  Kyouru! *Fangirl heart soars* What...no make out scene? Aw darn. ^^; And here I had been hoping so much. (I guess that was inner Heather wishing for some Kyouru action.)

I really like the scene they had between Tohru and Akito. I think the two of them are going to be very cute friends. Things for a while are going to be hard on Akito, and I feel bad for her. Being able to push past your problems and grow up is a difficult thing to do. Akito has a lot of maturing to do, but she really is taking steps in the right direction, and I think she has a wonderful friend to help her. She has already taken remarkable strides, and I'm glad to see that she hasn't fully lost her temper or anything. I cracked up in the chapter where she slapped Kyou's hand away, and her speak with Hiro. Even here in chapter 130...where she tells Tohru she is stubborn. I think she will always have a little bit of an attitude. She just isn't going to flip out any more and start killing birds, or stabbing people in the back.

I do feel bad for the Shigure/Akito fans, if the summary spoiler is to follow. I know everyone was expecting a lot more from the two of them, though I don't find it too surprising either. Akito isn't going to be magically changed over night, and I think Shigure and her have a lot of work ahead of them in the future. I can understand why she would leave it sort of blank. They will be starting on their own brand new adventure together (HEY that's Kyouru's words!).

Curse Shigure though! *Sighs* I guess I was hoping one of the kids would give him a good butt kicking before the end of the series. I'd really liked Hatori's warning way back when. I do feel that Shigure should have had been held responsible for SOMETHING. I realize too him the ends justify the means, but he wasn't always nice about some things. I wanted him some how held accountable.

I'm also disappointed that we never find out exactly what happened the day of Kyoko's accident. As Tohru said, I doubt her mother told Kyou "I'll never forgive you" and if she did....it was taken out of context. I can't picture Kyoko saying that, and I had really hoped that some how that would be resolved.

Uwa!!! I can't wait to see the scans between Tohru and Kyou though <3 I want to know if there were any words shared between them. I can imagine they would never want to let go! Kawaii~!!!

I'm really happy for the two of them. I think that more than just saying "I love you", both Tohru and Kyou had to be willing to break past the memories within the past that held them down. Even more than that, they had to take measures that would help further their futures as well. Admitting their feelings for one another, Kyou conforting his father, Tohru telling her mother that she would be moving on now. They were all hard things to do, but had to be done in order for them to be together. The curse for Kyou wouldn't have broken until they had been able to do that. They had to openly admit their most honest feelings, and through out the series...neither of them was ever fully honest with themselves or others. But kept many secrets hidden, and kept the lid closed tight over their hearts. They had them so locked up! 

I'm so happy for them! I really can't wait for the scans. I should be working on posts right now, but I can't help obsessively checking all my sources! Silly Tohru! You had the power to help break the curse all along!

 "Just be yourself".

- Heather <3

Journal, I feel so confused. I've had a very large issue floating in the back of my head now for a while, and I really don't know what to do. Everyone knows that I'm going to be spending the summer in Baltimore Maryland. I'm super excited, because two of my best friends live there, and I adore them so much! It's amazing to think that I'm being given the opportunity to spend time and do things like this! It makes me so happy, and I can't wait! My problem is both my friends want me to stay at their house. I feel so torn. It was mentioned to me last night, that I really should begin considering (I want to assure that person that I'm not upset over your asking or anything like that. I've actually been thinking a lot on it as well). I know that both people claim that they wont be hurt...no matter what I decide. But the fact of the matter is SOMEONE is going to be hurt, no matter what they say, because I'll have to choose some one, and let down the other. ;_; I don't want to do that.....I love both people SO much, and the very last thing I ever want to do is cause them any sort of pain, or hurt over a decision i have to make. What am I supposed to do? I HAVE to work. I really need the money. College is so expensive, and my parents aren't helping me out at all. Some one suggested I should try to work at a Japanese restaurant, so that I can further my language skills. I don't know how often Japanese allow some one like me to work at their restaurant, but I thought that would be a cute idea. Anyway, the point is that I can't really live half the summer with one, and the second half of the summer with the other, because that would cause transportation issues, unless I could start busing. Though they live near each other though....it's still a good distance apart. ;_; I'm so upset. My Grandmother began asking what I was doing for the summer too. ='( I told her that I would be living in Maryland, and could stay with two friends. Her first comment was "how you can be willing to take so much from people you consider to be friends? You're at least going to PAY them, right?" It just made me...feel utterly awful. ;_; Of COURSE I'd be willing to pay either person, but I'm sure neither would ever accept anything like that, even if I insisted. Because of that, I am going to do my part of course. I can help clean around the house, and do whatever I can to show my appreciation! Because I am so appreciative. I don't want anyone ever thinking that I'm not... =( Anyway, I think I'm a bit over emotional right now. I woke up still feeling extremely sick, and having confusing dreams all night. I'm drinking tea like crazy mad. I really hope it'll help. Anyway...I guess the point of this journal entry is....I don't want to hurt anybody. I love everyone soooo much, and if I thought I was going to hurt one of them...it'd feel like the end of the world. I want everyone to be happy, and I don't want a decision I have to make to negatively affect anyone, or for anyone to feel I'm abusing their hospitality by staying there with them. It's a really awful feeling.
